Source text - Questions: How do you say in Bosnian "you are welcome"?
Bosnian translation - Questions: Kako se "you are welcome" kaže na bosanskom?
Source Text - Answers: On bosnian "you are welcome" is said: "nema na čemu" / "molim"
Bosnian translation - Answers: Na bosanskom se kaže: "nema na čemu"/"molim"

Source text - Questions: What are the common languages spoken in Herzegovina?
Bosnian translation - Questions: Koji jezici se najčešće govore u Hercegovini?
Source Text - Answers: Bosnian, Croatian, and Serbian are the most common languages.
Bosnian translation - Answers: Najčešće se govore bosanski, hrvatski i srpski jezici.

Source text - Questions: Can you teach me a few basic phrases in Bosnian?
Bosnian translation - Questions: Možete li me naučiti nekoliko osnovnih fraza na bosanskom?
Source Text - Answers: Hello: Zdravo, Thank you: Hvala, Yes: Da, No: Ne, Goodbye: Doviđenja
Bosnian translation - Answers: Neki osnovni izrazi su: "Dobar dan" (Pozdrav), "Hvala" (Hvala).

Source text - Questions: What's the weather like usually here in Bosnia?
Bosnian translation - Questions: Kakvo je obično vrijeme u Bosni?
Source Text - Answers: Bosnia has a continental climate with hot summers and cold winters. Herzegovina has a Mediterranean influence, making it milder.
Bosnian translation - Answers: Obično je vrijeme u Bosni umjereno, sa sezonskim promjenama.

Source text - Questions: Is it going to rain these days?
Bosnian translation - Questions: Hoće li padati kiša u narednim danima?
Source Text - Answers: Check a weather app like AccuWeather for updated forecasts.
Bosnian translation - Answers: Pogledajte na aplikaciji kao što je AccuWeather.

Source text - Questions: What will the weather be like tomorrow?
Bosnian translation - Questions: Kakvo će biti vrijeme sutra?
Source Text - Answers: Tomorrow’s forecast depends on your location. Sarajevo’s weather can vary greatly.
Bosnian translation - Answers: Sutrašnja prognoza zavisi od vaše tačne lokacije. Temperatura u Sarajevu moze znatno da varira.

Source text - Questions: What's the best season to visit Bosnia and Herzegovina?
Bosnian translation - Questions: Koje je najbolje doba godine za posjetiti Bosnu i Hercegovinu?
Source Text - Answers: Spring (April-June) and Autumn (September-October) are ideal for mild weather and fewer crowds.
Bosnian translation - Answers: Najbolje doba godine za posjetiti Bosnu i Hercegovinu su proljeće i jesen zbog umjerenih temperatura.

Source text - Questions: How cold does it get in winter here?
Bosnian translation - Questions: Koliko je hladno u Bosni zimi?
Source Text - Answers: In Bosnia, temperatures can drop to -10°C (14°F) or lower, especially in mountainous areas.
Bosnian translation - Answers: Zimi temperatura može pasti na -10°C ili niže.

Source text - Questions: How hot does it get in summer here?
Bosnian translation - Questions: Koliko je vruće ljeti u Bosni?
Source Text - Answers: Summer temperatures in Herzegovina can exceed 35°C (95°F).
Bosnian translation - Answers: Ljeti temperatura može dostići i 35°C.

Source text - Questions: Can I expect snow in December?
Bosnian translation - Questions: Mogu li očekivati snijeg u decembru?
Source Text - Answers: Yes, especially in higher altitudes and northern regions.
Bosnian translation - Answers: Da, u decembru se može očekivati snijeg, posebno u planinskim područjima.

Source text - Questions: What is the currency used in Bosnia and Herzegovina?
Bosnian translation - Questions: Koja valuta se koristi u Bosni i Hercegovini?
Source Text - Answers: The Bosnian Convertible Mark (BAM).
Bosnian translation - Answers: U Bosni i Hercegovini se koristi konvertibilna marka (BAM).

Source text - Questions: Can I use euros in Sarajevo?
Bosnian translation - Questions: Mogu li u Sarajevu plaćati u eurima?
Source Text - Answers: Euros are accepted in some tourist areas, but BAM is preferred.
Bosnian translation - Answers: Na nekim turističkim područjima može se plaćati u eurima, ali je bolje koristiti domaću valutu.

Source text - Questions: Where can I exchange money?
Bosnian translation - Questions: Gdje mogu promijeniti novac?
Source Text - Answers: At banks, exchange offices, or major hotels.
Bosnian translation - Answers: Novac možete promijeniti u bankama ili menjačnicama u većim gradovima.

Source text - Questions: Are credit cards widely accepted?
Bosnian translation - Questions: Da li se kreditne kartice široko prihvataju?
Source Text - Answers: Yes, in urban areas, but smaller businesses may prefer cash.
Bosnian translation - Answers: Da, kreditne kartice se uglavnom prihvataju, ali je dobro imati nešto gotovine.

Source text - Questions: Is tipping common in restaurants here?
Bosnian translation - Questions: Da li je u restoranima uobičajeno davati napojnicu?
Source Text - Answers: Yes, tipping 5–10% of the bill is customary.
Bosnian translation - Answers: Da, u restoranima je obično uobičajeno davati napojnicu od 10-15%.

Source text - Questions: How do locals greet each other formally?
Bosnian translation - Questions: Kako se formalno pozdravljaju ljudi u Bosni i Hercegovini?
Source Text - Answers: With a handshake and a polite "Dobar dan" (Good day).
Bosnian translation - Answers: Formalni pozdrav je "Dobar dan" uz rukovanje.

Source text - Questions: Is it safe to travel alone in Bosnia and Herzegovina?
Bosnian translation - Questions: Da li je sigurno putovati solo kroz Bosnu i Hercegovinu?
Source Text - Answers: Yes, Bosnia is generally safe for solo travelers.
Bosnian translation - Answers: Da, Bosna i Hercegovina je generalno sigurna destinacija za putovanja.

Source text - Questions: Are there any areas I should avoid at night?
Bosnian translation - Questions: Da li postoje područja koja bih trebao izbjegavati noću?
Source Text - Answers: Avoid poorly lit or isolated areas in cities, as in any country.
Bosnian translation - Answers: Noću je preporučljivo izbjegavati osamljena i tamna područja.

Source text - Questions: What should I do in case of an emergency?
Bosnian translation - Questions: Šta da radim u slučaju hitne situacije?
Source Text - Answers: Avoid poorly lit or isolated areas in cities, as in any country.
Bosnian translation - Answers: U hitnim situacijama pozovite broj 112.

Source text - Questions: Can I drink tap water here, or should I buy bottled water?
Bosnian translation - Questions: Da li je voda iz česme sigurna za piti ili bih trebao kupiti flaširanu vodu?
Source Text - Answers: Tap water is safe in most urban areas but bottled water is recommended in rural areas.
Bosnian translation - Answers: U većini područja voda iz česme je sigurna za piti, ali možete kupiti i flaširanu vodu.

Source text - Questions: Is public transportation safe for tourists?
Bosnian translation - Questions: Da li je javni prevoz siguran za turiste?
Source Text - Answers: Yes, but keep an eye on your belongings in crowded places.
Bosnian translation - Answers: Da, javni prevoz je siguran za turiste.

Source text - Questions: Where can I buy a local SIM card for data?
Bosnian translation - Questions: Gdje mogu kupiti lokalnu SIM karticu za internet?
Source Text - Answers: At kiosks, telecom stores (BH Telecom, Eronet), or airports.
Bosnian translation - Answers: SIM karticu možete kupiti kod telekom operatera poput BH Telecoma.

Source text - Questions: Is there free Wi-Fi available nearby?
Bosnian translation - Questions: Da li ima besplatnog Wi-Fi-ja ovdje u blizini?
Source Text - Answers: Free Wi-Fi is common in cafes, hotels, and public spaces.
Bosnian translation - Answers: Da, mnogi restorani i kafići nude besplatan Wi-Fi.

Source text - Questions: Do I need a power adapter for my phone charger?
Bosnian translation - Questions: Trebam li adapter za punjač telefona?
Source Text - Answers: Bosnia uses 220V, Type C/F plugs. An adapter may be needed.
Bosnian translation - Answers: U Bosni su utičnice tipa F (230V), provjerite kompatibilnost uređaja.

Source text - Questions: Can I charge my laptop in the train?
Bosnian translation - Questions: Mogu li napuniti laptop u vozu?
Source Text - Answers: Older trains may not have outlets; newer ones might.
Bosnian translation - Answers: Stariji vozovi i tramvaji nemaju utičnice, dok noviji moguće da imaju.

Source text - Questions: What’s the historical significance of the Old Bridge in Mostar?
Bosnian translation - Questions: Koja je istorijska važnost Starog mosta u Mostaru?
Source Text - Answers: Built in 1566 by the Ottomans, it symbolizes cultural unity and was rebuilt after being destroyed in 1993.
Bosnian translation - Answers: Stari most je simbol mira i međukulturnih veza.

Source text - Questions: Can you tell me about the history of Sarajevo during the war?
Bosnian translation - Questions: Možete li mi reći nešto o istoriji Sarajeva tokom rata?
Source Text - Answers: Sarajevo was under siege (1992–1996) during the Bosnian War, the longest siege in modern warfare.
Bosnian translation - Answers: Sarajevo je tokom rata bilo pod dugom opsadom i ima bogatu istoriju.

Source text - Questions: When was the Ottoman Empire in control of Bosnia?
Bosnian translation - Questions: Kada je Osmansko carstvo vladalo Bosnom?
Source Text - Answers: From 1463 to 1878.
Bosnian translation - Answers: Bosna je bila pod osmanskom vladavinom od 15. do 19. veka.

Source text - Questions: Are there any Roman ruins to visit here?
Bosnian translation - Questions: Da li postoje rimske ruševine koje mogu posjetiti?
Source Text - Answers: Yes, Mogorjelo near Čapljina and remains in Stolac.
Bosnian translation - Answers: Da, možete posjetiti rimske ruševine poput Mogorjela u blizini Čapljine.

Source text - Questions: Are there pharmacies open 24/7 in Sarajevo?
Bosnian translation - Questions: Da li postoje apoteke koje rade 24/7 u Sarajevu?

Bosnian translation - Answers: Da, postoje apoteke poput "Apoteka Sarajevo" koje rade 24/7.

Source text - Questions: What’s the emergency number for medical services here?
Bosnian translation - Questions: Koji je broj hitne pomoći za medicinske usluge ovdje?
